\par <#/>}{\b\fs24\lang2057 The MP for Kasipul-Kabondo, Otieno K'Opiyo, was jailed for 12 months yesterday for forging documents from the Ministry of Agriculture and Livestock Development.
\par <#/>}{\fs24\lang2057 "The accused went out of his way to alter documents relating to products that he had bought from the Kenya Meat Commission," said Nairobi Chief Magistrate <-/Uniter> Pamela Kidullah.
\par <#/>The MP was found to have altered a figure of 25 cases of beef to 156.
\par <#/>Mrs Kidullah said the accused was a Member of Parliament but "the laws are not meant for the ordinary mortals while the <-/enacters> are above it.
