\par <#/>After failing to find any of the said guns, the officers took her to the police station and later to the district Special Branch office before being taken to the Provincial CID offices. <#/>She spent the night at Bondeni Police Station.
\par <#/>"I protested to them as they did not even allow me to put on my headscarf or shoes," she said, claiming that she was at times made to walk around the main town centres barefoot with her hair uncombed.
\par <#/>Mrs Wamwere said she had not seen her son since 1986 and was not aware if he was in Nairobi or elsewhere in the country prior to his arrest.
\par }\pard\plain \s46\qj\nowidctlpar\adjustright \lang2057 {<#/>"Why are these police officers asking me these questions and pestering me?" she asked in Kikuyu. <#/>She said they had been after Koigi 
ever since he got into politics and she did not see how she was involved.
\par }\pard\plain \qj\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20\lang1031 {\fs24\lang2057 <#/>"A man confides in his wife and not his mother," she said, adding that her son had not confided in her about his activities.
